35H265VpsSpsPpsTracker::FixedBitstream H265VpsSpsPpsTracker::CopyAndFixBitstream(rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> bitstream,
36 RTPVideoHeader* video_header_pointer) {
37 const uint8_t* data = bitstream.data();
38 const size_t data_size = bitstream.size();
39 RTPVideoHeader& video_header = *video_header_pointer;
40 RTC_DCHECK(video_header.codec == kVideoCodecH265);
41
42 auto& h265_header =
43 absl::get<RTPVideoHeaderH265>(video_header.video_type_header);
44
45 bool append_vps_sps_pps = false;
46 auto vps = vps_data_.end();
47 auto sps = sps_data_.end();
48 auto pps = pps_data_.end();
49
50 for (size_t i = 0; i < h265_header.nalus_length; ++i) {
51 const H265NaluInfo& nalu = h265_header.nalus[i];
52 switch (nalu.type) {
53 case H265::NaluType::kVps: {
54 vps_data_[nalu.vps_id].size = 0;
55 break;
56 }
57 case H265::NaluType::kSps: {
58 sps_data_[nalu.sps_id].vps_id = nalu.vps_id;
59 sps_data_[nalu.sps_id].width = video_header.width;
60 sps_data_[nalu.sps_id].height = video_header.height;
61 break;
62 }
63 case H265::NaluType::kPps: {
64 pps_data_[nalu.pps_id].sps_id = nalu.sps_id;
65 break;
66 }
67 case H265::NaluType::kIdrWRadl:
68 case H265::NaluType::kIdrNLp:
69 case H265::NaluType::kCra: {
70 // If this is the first packet of an IDR, make sure we have the required
71 // SPS/PPS and also calculate how much extra space we need in the buffer
72 // to prepend the SPS/PPS to the bitstream with start codes.
73 if (video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame) {
74 if (nalu.pps_id == -1) {
75 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "No PPS id in IDR nalu.";
76 return {kRequestKeyframe};
77 }
78
79 pps = pps_data_.find(nalu.pps_id);
80 if (pps == pps_data_.end()) {
81 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
82 << "No PPS with id " << nalu.pps_id << " received";
83 return {kRequestKeyframe};
84 }
85
86 sps = sps_data_.find(pps->second.sps_id);
87 if (sps == sps_data_.end()) {
88 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
89 << "No SPS with id << " << pps->second.sps_id << " received";
90 return {kRequestKeyframe};
91 }
92
93 vps = vps_data_.find(sps->second.vps_id);
94 if (vps == vps_data_.end()) {
95 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
96 << "No VPS with id " << sps->second.vps_id << " received";
97 return {kRequestKeyframe};
98 }
99
100 // Since the first packet of every keyframe should have its width and
101 // height set we set it here in the case of it being supplied out of
102 // band.
103 video_header.width = sps->second.width;
104 video_header.height = sps->second.height;
105
106 // If the VPS/SPS/PPS was supplied out of band then we will have saved
107 // the actual bitstream in |data|.
108 // This branch is not verified.
109 if (vps->second.data && sps->second.data && pps->second.data) {
110 RTC_DCHECK_GT(vps->second.size, 0);
111 RTC_DCHECK_GT(sps->second.size, 0);
112 RTC_DCHECK_GT(pps->second.size, 0);
113 append_vps_sps_pps = true;
114 }
115 }
116 break;
117 }
118 default:
119 break;
120 }
121 }
122
123 RTC_CHECK(!append_vps_sps_pps ||
124 (sps != sps_data_.end() && pps != pps_data_.end()));
125
126 // Calculate how much space we need for the rest of the bitstream.
127 size_t required_size = 0;
128
129 if (append_vps_sps_pps) {
130 required_size += vps->second.size + sizeof(start_code_h265);
131 required_size += sps->second.size + sizeof(start_code_h265);
132 required_size += pps->second.size + sizeof(start_code_h265);
133 }
134
135 if (h265_header.packetization_type == kH265AP) {
136 const uint8_t* nalu_ptr = data + 1;
137 while (nalu_ptr < data + data_size) {
138 RTC_DCHECK(video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame);
139 required_size += sizeof(start_code_h265);
140
141 // The first two bytes describe the length of a segment.
142 uint16_t segment_length = nalu_ptr[0] << 8 | nalu_ptr[1];
143 nalu_ptr += 2;
144
145 required_size += segment_length;
146 nalu_ptr += segment_length;
147 }
148 } else {
149 if (video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame)
150 required_size += sizeof(start_code_h265);
151 required_size += data_size;
152 }
153
154 // Then we copy to the new buffer.
155 FixedBitstream fixed;
156 fixed.bitstream.EnsureCapacity(required_size);
157
158 if (append_vps_sps_pps) {
159 // Insert VPS.
160 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(start_code_h265);
161 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(vps->second.data.get(), vps->second.size);
162
163 // Insert SPS.
164 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(start_code_h265);
165 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(sps->second.data.get(), sps->second.size);
166
167 // Insert PPS.
168 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(start_code_h265);
169 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(pps->second.data.get(), pps->second.size);
170
171 // Update codec header to reflect the newly added SPS and PPS.
172 H265NaluInfo vps_info;
173 vps_info.type = H265::NaluType::kVps;
174 vps_info.vps_id = vps->first;
175 vps_info.sps_id = -1;
176 vps_info.pps_id = -1;
177 H265NaluInfo sps_info;
178 sps_info.type = H265::NaluType::kSps;
179 sps_info.vps_id = vps->first;
180 sps_info.sps_id = sps->first;
181 sps_info.pps_id = -1;
182 H265NaluInfo pps_info;
183 pps_info.type = H265::NaluType::kPps;
184 pps_info.vps_id = vps->first;
185 pps_info.sps_id = sps->first;
186 pps_info.pps_id = pps->first;
187 if (h265_header.nalus_length + 2 <= kMaxNalusPerPacket) {
188 h265_header.nalus[h265_header.nalus_length++] = vps_info;
189 h265_header.nalus[h265_header.nalus_length++] = sps_info;
190 h265_header.nalus[h265_header.nalus_length++] = pps_info;
191 } else {
192 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Not enough space in H.265 codec header to insert "
193 "SPS/PPS provided out-of-band.";
194 }
195 }
196
197 // Copy the rest of the bitstream and insert start codes.
198 if (h265_header.packetization_type == kH265AP) {
199 const uint8_t* nalu_ptr = data + 1;
200 while (nalu_ptr < data + data_size) {
201 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(start_code_h265);
202
203 // The first two bytes describe the length of a segment.
204 uint16_t segment_length = nalu_ptr[0] << 8 | nalu_ptr[1];
205 nalu_ptr += 2;
206
207 size_t copy_end = nalu_ptr - data + segment_length;
208 if (copy_end > data_size) {
209 return {kDrop};
210 }
211
212 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(nalu_ptr, segment_length);
213 nalu_ptr += segment_length;
214 }
215 } else {
216 if (video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame) {
217 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(start_code_h265);
218 }
219 fixed.bitstream.AppendData(bitstream.data(), bitstream.size());
220 }
221
222 fixed.action = kInsert;
223 return fixed;
224}

226void H265VpsSpsPpsTracker::InsertVpsSpsPpsNalus(
227 const std::vector<uint8_t>& vps,
228 const std::vector<uint8_t>& sps,
229 const std::vector<uint8_t>& pps) {
230 constexpr size_t kNaluHeaderOffset = 1;
231 if (vps.size() < kNaluHeaderOffset) {
232 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "VPS size " << vps.size() << " is smaller than "
233 << kNaluHeaderOffset;
234 return;
235 }
236 if ((vps[0] & 0x7e) >> 1 != H265::NaluType::kSps) {
237 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SPS Nalu header missing";
238 return;
239 }
240 if (sps.size() < kNaluHeaderOffset) {
241 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SPS size " << sps.size() << " is smaller than "
242 << kNaluHeaderOffset;
243 return;
244 }
245 if ((sps[0] & 0x7e) >> 1 != H265::NaluType::kSps) {
246 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SPS Nalu header missing";
247 return;
248 }
249 if (pps.size() < kNaluHeaderOffset) {
250 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "PPS size " << pps.size() << " is smaller than "
251 << kNaluHeaderOffset;
252 return;
253 }
254 if ((pps[0] & 0x7e) >> 1 != H265::NaluType::kPps) {
255 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SPS Nalu header missing";
256 return;
257 }
258 absl::optional<H265VpsParser::VpsState> parsed_vps = H265VpsParser::ParseVps(
259 vps.data() + kNaluHeaderOffset, vps.size() - kNaluHeaderOffset);
260 absl::optional<H265SpsParser::SpsState> parsed_sps = H265SpsParser::ParseSps(
261 sps.data() + kNaluHeaderOffset, sps.size() - kNaluHeaderOffset);
262 absl::optional<H265PpsParser::PpsState> parsed_pps = H265PpsParser::ParsePps(
263 pps.data() + kNaluHeaderOffset, pps.size() - kNaluHeaderOffset);
264
265 if (!parsed_vps) {
266 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to parse VPS.";
267 }
268
269 if (!parsed_sps) {
270 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to parse SPS.";
271 }
272
273 if (!parsed_pps) {
274 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to parse PPS.";
275 }
276
277 if (!parsed_vps || !parsed_pps || !parsed_sps) {
278 return;
279 }
280
281 VpsInfo vps_info;
282 vps_info.size = vps.size();
283 uint8_t* vps_data = new uint8_t[vps_info.size];
284 memcpy(vps_data, vps.data(), vps_info.size);
285 vps_info.data.reset(vps_data);
286 vps_data_[parsed_vps->id] = std::move(vps_info);
287
288 SpsInfo sps_info;
289 sps_info.size = sps.size();
290 sps_info.width = parsed_sps->width;
291 sps_info.height = parsed_sps->height;
292 sps_info.vps_id = parsed_sps->vps_id;
293 uint8_t* sps_data = new uint8_t[sps_info.size];
294 memcpy(sps_data, sps.data(), sps_info.size);
295 sps_info.data.reset(sps_data);
296 sps_data_[parsed_sps->id] = std::move(sps_info);
297
298 PpsInfo pps_info;
299 pps_info.size = pps.size();
300 pps_info.sps_id = parsed_pps->sps_id;
301 uint8_t* pps_data = new uint8_t[pps_info.size];
302 memcpy(pps_data, pps.data(), pps_info.size);
303 pps_info.data.reset(pps_data);
304 pps_data_[parsed_pps->id] = std::move(pps_info);
305
306 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Inserted SPS id " << parsed_sps->id << " and PPS id "
307 << parsed_pps->id << " (referencing SPS "
308 << parsed_pps->sps_id << ")";
309}
